720422f-a.title: Manhattan: Hester Street - Mulberry Street
720422f-a.text:
No. 185 Hester Street, north side, between Mulberry and Mott Streets;
showing the display of the Pope's Crown and Keys, during the Feast of San
Gennaro.
September 21, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

720423f-a.title: Manhattan: Hester Street - Mulberry Street
720423f-a.text:
Heater Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Mulberry
Street. No. 178 Hester Street, adjoining the S.E. corner of Mulberry
Street, is a 3-story frame house with a brick front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 534.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
